# Connection phases to execute (space-separated list).
#
# Phases are executed in order during VPN connection. Each phase
# is a reusable component that outputs shell commands for connect.sh.
#
# Built-in phases:
#   firewall - Configure packet filter (PF) tables and rules
#   vpn      - Bring up VPN interface (protocol-specific)
#   dns      - Configure DNS resolution
#
# User-provided phases:
#   Place custom phase scripts in ${VPN_SWITCH_BASE}/.include/phase/
#   Example: .include/phase/custom_routing_up.sh
#
# Phase resolution order (for phase "foo"):
#   1. User override: .include/phase/foo_up.sh (if exists)
#   2. Protocol-specific: phase_${protocol}_foo_up() function
#   3. Generic: phase_foo_up() function
#
# Usage:
#   - Connect uses phases with "_up" suffix
#   - Disconnect uses same phases with "_down" suffix (reversed order)
#   - Customize by editing .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_PHASES_CONNECT
